race.comment: HURRICANE MIST (5) is a capable type and proved too strong last time to win by a neck at this track in a handy 28.50 beating Montana Icon. Ran one of the fastest times on the program in her latest win. Expected to go well again. ELSA JAY (2) has some solid form under her belt and proved too classy last time to win by 1.5 lengths at Shepparton in a handy 26.01 beating Rock The Marjen. Consistent performer from this draw with a win and six minor placings to her credit. Sure to be thereabouts. LEAVE ME IN (8) has missed the placings at her last couple but was in the money three back when third (28.95) at this track in a Grade 5. Well placed here and can atone this time. MCIVOR JEWELS (7) is worth consideration.
